                        <collation>The codex has been refoliated. The references in the Catalogue (and in Steinschneider's detailed de-scription in HB) must now be amended, as follows:
                           For 'fol. 28b read fol. 33v; '63', 73; '70b, 8ov; '96, 
                           106v; '97', 107; '111', 121; '112¹, 122v; ‘114", 124V;
                           '115', 125; '115, 125v; ‘116b, 126v; '117¹, 127V;
                           ‘119', 129; ‘121', 131; ‘122', 132; ‘145¹, 155V; ‘146',
                           156; 147¹, 157V; '148, 158v; '149', 159; '150', 160;
                           ‘153', 163; ‘153¹, 163v; ‘156b, 166v; ‘157', 167; ‘159',
                           169; ‘160', 170; ‘165', 175; ‘176b¹, 186v.</collation>
                     </supportDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                     <summary>Ashkenazic square script</summary>
                     <handNote>The acrostic of the name Menahem is pointed out on <locus>fol. 65r</locus>. This scribe copied up to <locus>fol. 124v</locus> 
                        (or perhaps up to <locus>fol. 128v</locus>, end of the quire). <locus>Fols. 129r-155r</locus> are copied by another hand, 
                        and <locus>fols. 155v-168v</locus> by several different hands (but <locus>fols. 155v-156v</locus> may well be by the hand of the main
                        copyist). <locus>Fols. 169-188</locus> (formerly 159-178) are part of another MS., written in a cursive (French?) hand, probably about the same period.</handNote>
                  </handDesc>

